    {
        "content": "<p>Oh neat, I didn't know he was here.</p>",
        "id": 197424989,
        "sender_full_name": "Oscar Cunningham",
        "timestamp": 1589382011
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I also know that <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"277318\">@Ivan Di Liberti</span> has worked on this topic since he presented a talk related Ionads at CT last year. (Sorry that the best I can do is invite other people to answer <span aria-label=\"joy\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f602\" role=\"img\" title=\"joy\">:joy:</span> )</p>",
        "id": 197427590,
        "sender_full_name": "Morgan Rogers (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1589383111
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ivan's thesis draft (<a href=\"https://diliberti.github.io/Research.html\">https://diliberti.github.io/Research.html</a>) has some good info on ionads (in particular it allows large ionads, contra Garner), but I don't think it answers this question</p>",
        "id": 197428222,
        "sender_full_name": "Oscar Cunningham",
        "timestamp": 1589383319
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I recently updated the thesis with a (almost) stable version (<a href=\"https://diliberti.github.io/phdthesis.pdf\">https://diliberti.github.io/phdthesis.pdf</a>). By the end of the month, I hope to push something on the ArXiv. <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"277473\">@[Mod] Morgan Rogers</span>  mentioned me a couple of times already, thus, since I have achieved a semi-stable version of it, I feel the duty of informing you.</p>",
        "id": 209193889,
        "sender_full_name": "Ivan Di Liberti",
        "timestamp": 1599336357
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for the update... I've been looking at your thesis a lot lately. I am referring to it in a work in progress so it's good to know that it will be on arxiv soon.</p>",
